Install Heroku CLI
then create an app using Herok create
then instigate requirements using pip freeze requirements.txt
then git add, commit, finally push it to heroku master

the URL will be shown in the bottom

steps:
- heroku login
- heroku create (not needed if already created)
- git add and commit
- git push to heroku master

to verify:
- say 
  - heroku apps (this will give the url of the app created)
- now to set
  - heroku git:remote -a <app url shown in the result for the above query
- verify using git remote -v
- git push heroku master